":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to knock, to hack, to dig into, to tap, to peck; literally"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to knock, to hack, to dig into, to tap, to peck; so as investigating, to dig into, to tap"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to knock, to hack, to dig into, to tap, to peck; so as making a certain sound, to click (also on the computer), to knock, to thump, pluck (a drum as well as a string instrument)","examples":[{"text":"جِلَّوْز عَيْن الثَّوْر\nشَيْئًا مَلْهَوِيّ\nيَنْقُر لَك فَالْبَاب\nنَقْرً مُسْتَوِيّ\nيَصَّدَّع رَأْسَك\nفَذَاك الدَوِيّ\nوَرِزْق الْجِلَّوْز\nفَذَاك الصُّدَاع","english":"Filberts and prunes\nare frolic forsooth!\nYour door is pinged\nto have them slinged,\nstopless din and ballyhoo!\nEach cobnut wreaks you grue!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike, to knock, to hack, to dig into, to tap, to peck; so as offending a person, to injure, to bully"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig into, to peck, to stipple, to pit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَقَرَ (naqara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Latin fodere for semantical development. Cognate to the Hebrew root ניקר / נִקֵּר (nikér, “to bore, gouge out”)"},"ipa":null}